ue is preventing us from hitting the API endpoint since it's not applying the static-prefix to the API endpoints.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mlflow/mlflow/issues/comments/917295124/reactions","total_count":2,"+1":2,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"akuma12","id":969848,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk2OTg0OA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/969848?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/akuma12","html_url":"https://github.com/akuma12","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/akuma12/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/akuma12/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/akuma12/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/akuma12/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/akuma12/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/akuma12/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/akuma12/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/akuma12/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/akuma12/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mlflow/mlflow/issues/comments/919377871","html_url":"https://github.com/mlflow/mlflow/issues/4484#issuecomment-919377871","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mlflow/mlflow/issues/4484","id":919377871,"node_id":"IC_kwDOCB5Jx842zJfP","user":{"login":"akuma12","id":969848,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk2OTg0OA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/969848?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/akuma12","html_url":"https://github.com/akuma12","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/akuma12/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/akuma12/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/akuma12/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/akuma12/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/akuma12/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/akuma12/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/akuma12/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/akuma12/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/akuma12/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2021-09-14T17:47:47Z","updated_at":"2021-09-14T18:07:08Z","author_association":"NONE","body":"While I still need to use `--static-prefix mlflow`, I was able to work around this for now with some creative use of an NGINX reverse proxy:\r\n```\r\n# Define the parameters for a specific virtual host/server\r\nserver {\r\n    # Define the server name, IP address, and/or port of the server\r\n    listen 8080;\r\n\r\n    # Define the specified charset to the “Content-Type” response header field\r\n    charset utf-8;\r\n\r\n    # Send requests starting with `/mlflow/api` to `/api`\r\n    location ^~ /mlflow/api/ {\r\n        # Define the location of the proxy server to send the request to\r\n        proxy_pass http://mlflow:5000/api/;\r\n\r\n        # Redefine the header fields that NGINX sends to the upstream server\r\n        proxy_set_header Host $host;\r\n        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;\r\n        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    # Send other requests to `/mlflow`\r\n    location /mlflow/ {\r\n        # Define the location of the proxy server to send the request to\r\n        proxy_pass http://mlflow:5000/mlflow/;\r\n\r\n        # Redefine the header fields that NGINX sends to the upstream server\r\n        proxy_set_header Host $host;\r\n        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;\r\n        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mlflow/mlflow/issues/comments/9193778